<header>
<h1 class="title">Vim Tips</h1>
</header><p>
Below are the following commands that may help you. If you ever get
stuck, type <code>:help</code> for more information.
</p>

<p>
<b><b>Normal Mode</b></b> is the default mode when entering Vim. This mode is
mainly used for altering text. If not in Normal Mode, press <code>Esc</code> or
<code>&lt;C-[&gt;</code> to return. Also, you can use these commands to exit any mode and
return to Normal Mode.
</p>

<div id="outline-container-org455e972" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org455e972">Motion</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org455e972">
<p>
These are the basic movements.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>[hjkl]</code> - move [left, bottom, top, right]</li>
<li><code>g[hjkl]</code> - move [left, bottom, top, right] on display lines</li>
</ul>

<p>
The following movements allow a greater range of mobility.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>w | W</code> - next word</li>
<li><code>b | B</code> - previous word</li>
<li><code>e | E</code> - end of current word</li>
<li><code>ge | gE</code> - end of previous word</li>
<li><code>[g]0</code> - move to start of [display] line</li>
<li><code>&gt;[g]^</code> - move to first non-whitespace character of [display] line</li>
<li><code>[g]$</code> - move to end of [display] line</li>
<li><code>%</code> - jump to matching tag</li>
<li><code>(/)</code> - jump to start/end of next sentence</li>
<li><code>{/}</code> - jump to start/end of next paragraph</li>
<li><code>H/M/L</code> - jump to top/middle/bottom of screen</li>
<li><code>gf</code> - jump to filename under cursor</li>
<li><code>gg</code> - jump to start of file</li>
<li><code>G</code> - jump to end of file</li>
<li><code>zz</code> - redraws to middle of screen</li>
<li><code>z[tzb]</code> - redraw to [top, middle, bottom] of screen</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-]&gt;</code> - jump to definition of keyword under cursor</li>
</ul>

<p>
If you make any changes while in Normal Mode, the following commands
will help.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>.</code> - repeat last change</li>
<li><code>u</code> - undo change</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-r&gt;</code> - redo change</li>
<li><code>g[;,]</code> - traverse backward/forward through each change</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgdbe9870" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgdbe9870">Marks</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgdbe9870">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>m[a-zA-Z]</code> - make mark</li>
<li><code>'[mark]</code> - jump to mark - <code>`</code> for exact column</li>
<li><code>'.</code> - jump to last change</li>
<li><code>'’</code> - jump to last position</li>
<li><code>'^</code> - jump to last insertion</li>
<li><code>'[</code> - jump to start of last change/yank</li>
<li><code>']</code> - jump to end of last change/yank</li>
<li><code>'&lt;</code> - jump to start of visual selection</li>
<li><code>'&gt;</code> - jump to end of visual selection</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orga128f3d" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orga128f3d">Editing</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orga128f3d">
<p>
The following commands will allow you to edit text in various ways.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>~</code> - toggle case</li>
<li><code>ga</code> - show numeric code for current character</li>
<li><code>x</code> - delete character</li>
<li><code>J</code> - join lines together</li>
<li><code>#[&lt;C-a&gt; | &lt;C-x&gt;]</code> - [add, subtract] #</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgad2fdd5" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgad2fdd5">Buffers</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgad2fdd5">
<p>
You can also navigate through buffers/jump list with these commands.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-o&gt;</code> - move to previous buffer/jump</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-i&gt;</code> - move to next buffer/jump</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-^&gt;</code> - switch alternate buffers</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-g&gt;</code> - echo name &amp; status of current buffer</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org65606c0" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org65606c0">Windows</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org65606c0">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org6daf547" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org6daf547">Splitting</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org6daf547">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;s</code> - split horizontally</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;v</code> - split vertically</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org77e003f" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org77e003f">Changing Focus</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org77e003f">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;w</code> - cycle through open windows</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;[hjkl]</code> - focus [left, bottom, top, right] window</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org8398d3a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org8398d3a">Closing</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org8398d3a">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;c</code> - close active window</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;o</code> - keep only active window</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgdb20565" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgdb20565">Resizing</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgdb20565">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;=</code> - equalize width/height of all windows</li>
<li><code>#&lt;C-w&gt;_</code> - maximize or set active window height to # rows</li>
<li><code>#&lt;C-w&gt;|</code> - maximize or set active window width to # columns</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;[+-]</code> - [decrease, increase] active window height by 1 line</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgbe2748e" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgbe2748e">Moving</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgbe2748e">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;r</code> - rotate all windows</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;x</code> - swap current window with neighbor</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;[HJKL]</code> - move current window to [left, bottom, top, right]</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;T</code> - move split window into new tab</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org4e6d41b" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org4e6d41b">Tabs</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org4e6d41b">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>gt</code> - move to next tab</li>
<li><code>gT</code> - move to previous tab</li>
<li><code>#gt</code> - move to tab #</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org6e80db6" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org6e80db6">Other Modes</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org6e80db6">
<p>
<b><b>Replace Mode</b></b> is a mode where you can change text without inserting
anything. The following commands will allow you to access this mode.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>R</code> - enter Replace Mode</li>
<li><code>r</code> - replace character</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Virtual Replace Mode</b></b> is just like Replace Mode but can act on tabs
and whitespace as if they were spaces.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>gR</code> - enter Virtual Replace Mode</li>
<li><code>gr</code> - replace virtual character</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Operator-Pending Mode</b></b> is a mode that you briefly enter when typing
the following commands.
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgff426ab" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgff426ab">Editing</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgff426ab">
<p>
These commands are usually appended by a motion. Some commands act on a
line when typed twice.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>c</code> - change</li>
<li><code>d</code> - delete</li>
<li><code>y</code> - yank</li>
<li><code>[&lt;&gt;]</code> - shift [left, right]</li>
<li><code>=</code> - autoindent</li>
<li><code>g~</code> - swap case</li>
<li><code>gu</code> - lowercase</li>
<li><code>gU</code> - uppercase</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgfb4bd84" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgfb4bd84">Character Search</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgfb4bd84">
<p>
These commands act on following characters and may be used to move
around more efficiently.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>f</code> - find next character</li>
<li><code>F</code> - find previous character</li>
<li><code>t</code> - find until next character</li>
<li><code>T</code> - find until previous character</li>
<li><code>;</code> - go to next character</li>
<li><code>,</code> - go to previous character</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org8334c8f" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org8334c8f">Other</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org8334c8f">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>q</code> - record macro</li>
<li><code>@</code> - start macro</li>
<li><code>!</code> - filter through external program</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Insert Mode</b></b> is used for inserting text. The following commands will
send you to Insert Mode.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>i</code> - insert at character</li>
<li><code>gi</code> - insert at last insertion</li>
<li><code>I</code> - insert at start of line</li>
<li><code>a</code> - append after character</li>
<li><code>A</code> - append at end of line</li>
<li><code>C</code> - change line</li>
<li><code>o</code> - new line below</li>
<li><code>O</code> - new line above</li>
<li><code>s</code> - substitute character</li>
<li><code>S</code> - substitute line</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Insert Normal Mode</b></b> is a quick way to do a Normal Command before
returning to Insert Mode. Just press <code>&lt;C-o&gt;</code> to go to Normal Mode for
just one command.
</p>

<p>
<b><b>Visual Mode</b></b> is utilized for selecting and operating on text. The
following commands will send you to Visual Mode. You can exit normally
or also press the following commands again.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>v</code> - enter character-wise Visual Mode</li>
<li><code>V</code> - enter line-wise Visual Mode</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-v&gt;</code> - enter block-wise Visual Mode</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgb8bdb84" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgb8bdb84">Editing</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgb8bdb84">
<p>
You can also interact with your selection and make changes.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>gv</code> - reselect last visual selection</li>
<li><code>o</code> - go to alternate end of selection</li>
<li><code>U</code> - uppercase selection</li>
<li><code>u</code> - lowercase selection</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Command Mode</b></b> allow you to make greater changes with Ex commands. To
enter this mode, press ':'.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>p[rint]</code> - echo current line</li>
<li><code>join</code> - join lines</li>
<li><code>yank [register]</code> - yank into register</li>
<li><code>put [register]</code> - put text from register after line</li>
<li><code>co[py]/t [address]</code> - copy lines to to below specififiedy by</li>
</ul>
<p>
address
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>m[ove] [address]</code> - move lines to to below specififiedy by address</li>
<li><code>delete [register]</code> - delete into register</li>
<li><code>norm[al] [command]</code> - execute normal command</li>
<li><code>s[ubstitute]/[pattern]/[string]/[flags]</code> - substitute</li>
<li><code>&amp;</code> - repeat substitution</li>
<li><code>global/[pattern]/[cmd]</code> - execute command on specified lines where</li>
</ul>
<p>
pattern matches
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>vglobal</code></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgabefd0b" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgabefd0b">Motion &amp; Selection</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgabefd0b">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>#</code> - specify line</li>
<li><code>%</code> - entire file range/current file name</li>
<li><code>0</code> - beginning of file</li>
<li><code>$</code> - end of file</li>
<li><code>.</code> - current line</li>
<li><code>‘&lt;,’&gt;</code> - visual range</li>
<li><code>[start],[end]</code> - specify range</li>
<li><code>[address] + n</code> - offset range</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org9c26f75" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org9c26f75">Navigation</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org9c26f75">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>[&lt;C-p&gt; | &lt;C-n&gt;]</code> - go to [previous, next] command</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-r&gt;&lt;C-w&gt;</code> - copies current word into prompt</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-d&gt;</code> - autocomplete</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgc8ab5e6" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgc8ab5e6">Shell</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgc8ab5e6">
<p>
<b><b>Note</b></b>: To use the shell, it's recommended to use <code>&lt;C-z&gt;</code> &amp; <code>fg</code>
instead.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>!</code> - run shell commands</li>
<li><code>shell</code> - enter shell session</li>
<li><code>pwd</code> - print working directory</li>
<li><code>cd</code> - change directory</li>
<li><code>find</code> - open file</li>
<li><code>set path+=[subdir]</code> - specify directories Vim will look in</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgd4b22f1" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgd4b22f1">Buffers</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgd4b22f1">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>bp[revious]/bn[ext]</code> - interact with buffer list</li>
<li><code>b[uffer] #</code> - go to specified buffer</li>
<li><code>bufdo</code> - execute Ex command in all buffers</li>
<li><code>bd[elete]</code> - delete buffer</li>
<li><code>ls</code> - shows content of buffer list</li>
<li><code>%</code> - filepath of active buffer - appending ':h' removes the</li>
</ul>
<p>
filename
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orgeeeea3d" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgeeeea3d">Argument List</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgeeeea3d">
<p>
<b><b>Note</b></b>: May use globbing and backtick expansion.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>args</code> - list arguments</li>
<li><code>first</code> - go to first arg</li>
<li><code>next/prev[ious]</code> - navigate files in args</li>
<li><code>argdo</code> - execute same command on each buffer in the set</li>
<li><code>cfdo</code> - execute command in each file on quickfix list</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org5bb6797" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org5bb6797">Files</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org5bb6797">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>e[dit]</code> - create new file</li>
<li><code>w[rite]</code> - save file/take buffer content into input</li>
<li><code>wn[ext]</code> - save current file &amp; edit next file</li>
<li><code>up[date]</code> - save file only if buffer is modified</li>
<li><code>read</code> - take output into buffer</li>
<li><code>E[xplore]</code> - open file explorer for directory of active buffer</li>
<li><code>Sex[plore]</code> - open file explorer horizontally</li>
<li><code>Vex[plore]</code> - open file explorer vertically</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org2e29be2" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org2e29be2">Tabs</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2e29be2">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>tabe[dit] [file]</code> - open file in new tab</li>
<li><code>tabc[lose]</code> - close current tab</li>
<li><code>tabo[nly]</code> - keep only current tab</li>
<li><code>tabn[ext] #</code> - go to tab # or next tab</li>
<li><code>tabp[revious]</code> - go to previous tab</li>
<li><code>tabl[ast]</code> - go to last tab</li>
<li><code>tabmove #</code> - move tab</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org7b773f7" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org7b773f7">Windows</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org7b773f7">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>sp[lit] [file]</code> - split window horizontally &amp; create new buffer</li>
<li><code>vsp[lit] [file]</code> - split window vertically &amp; create new buffer</li>
<li><code>clo[se]/q[uit]</code> - close active window</li>
<li><code>on[ly]</code> - keep only active window</li>
<li><code>lcd [path]</code> - set local working directory in window</li>
<li><code>windo lcd [path]</code> - set local working directory for all windows in</li>
</ul>
<p>
tab
</p>

<p>
<b><b>Command Line Window Mode</b></b> opens a buffer that allows you to edit its
specified history.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>q:</code> - enter command line window with Ex commands history</li>
<li><code>q/</code> - enter command line window with search history</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-f&gt;</code> - switch to command line window</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Search Mode</b></b> is a way to search for long text.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>*</code> - search current word</li>
<li><code>/</code> - search forward</li>
<li><code>?</code> - search backward</li>
<li><code>K</code> - search current word for man page</li>
<li><code>n</code> - go to next search</li>
<li><code>N</code> - repeat previous search</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Insert &amp; Command Modes</b></b> have some commands in common listed below.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-h&gt;</code> - backspace</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-w&gt;</code> - delete back one word</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-u&gt;</code> - delete back to start of line</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org929a441" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org929a441">Registers</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org929a441">
<p>
<b><b>Note:</b></b> prepend u to four-digit hexadecimal code
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>&lt;C-r&gt;[register]</code> - paste from specified register</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-r&gt;&lt;C-p&gt;[register]</code> - paste unformatted text</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-v&gt;[code]</code> - convert to character</li>
<li><code>&lt;C-k&gt;[digraph]</code> - convert character</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Expression Register</b></b> is a unique register to do quick calculations
and more. Just press <code>&lt;C-r&gt;=</code> to enter.
</p>

<p>
In addition to these modes, there are more features to Vim.
</p>

<p>
<b><b>Macros</b></b> introduce a way to record multiple commands.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>@:</code> - repeat Ex command</li>
<li><code>@@</code> - repeat macro</li>
</ul>

<p>
<b><b>Text Objects</b></b> allow for greater control over which text to operate
on.
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>a[w, t, p, ) | b, } | B, ], &gt;, ’, ", `]</code> - around [word, tag,</li>
</ul>
<p>
paragraph, (), {}, [], '', "", ``]
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>i[w, t, p, ) | b, } | B, ], &gt;, ', ", `]</code> - in [word, tag,</li>
</ul>
<p>
paragraph, (), {}, [], '', "", ``]
